    "body": "Looking at https://github.com/spack/spack/blob/develop/lib/spack/env/cc#L273, `spackcc` assumes that headers are always in `<prefix>/include`, which isn't always the case. Especially for external package on Debian/Ubuntu some headers live in e.g. `/usr/lib/x86_64-linux-gnu/openmpi/include/`.\r\n\r\nSee #7255 for an example.\r\n\r\n",
